:'''Vaska:''' ...I heard that a sequel is going to come out. Artem might... Ah, sorry. I thought you were asking about the Tale of the Winterlands.
:'''Vaska:''' I guess... I've been doing alright? The florist has been a bit busier these days, so I haven't had as much time to read as before. It's been a headache.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Is the florist selling anything new?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501024185-->
::'''Vaska:''' Nah. I haven't cultivated any new varieties, but we've had a lot less snow recently, and the temperature is starting to go back up. Some flowers have blossomed splendidly. It could be a good chance for the shop to put together some sales promotions.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Is that book's ban... going to get lifted?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_501024187-->
::'''Vaska:''' You mean the Tale of the Winterlands? I'm not sure. But that's the rumor that has been circulating among us book fans. I don't know if it's true or not.
::'''Vaska:''' I've heard that the Town Hall is getting ready to develop the outskirts of the city. They've apparently dispatched people to explore that area. If that's true, then there's no need to ban that series...
:<!--Ends the current performance-->
:'''Vaska:''' Nice to see you again! Vaska at your service. If you need some help picking the right flowers, feel free to let me know.
:<!--Ends the current performance-->
:'''Vaska:''' No rush. Take your time.
:<!--Ends the current performance-->
;(First interaction)
